WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Flying Home by Stephen Rabley Penguin Readers, Easy Start.

00:07.000 --> 00:29.000
Felix is a blue and yellow bird from Brazil.

00:29.000 --> 00:33.000
He lives with the Baxter family in New York.

00:33.000 --> 00:36.000
His home is a big cage.

00:36.000 --> 00:40.000
It's on the 40th floor of a tall building.

00:40.000 --> 00:45.000
Felix likes the Baxters and the Baxters like him.

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
They give him food.

00:47.000 --> 00:51.000
They talk to him and show him to all their friends.

00:51.000 --> 00:58.000
But Felix isn't happy. He wants to go home to Brazil.

00:58.000 --> 01:03.000
Every night, Felix looks up at the sky.

01:03.000 --> 01:06.000
He can see the whole city.

01:06.000 --> 01:09.000
It's big and exciting.

01:09.000 --> 01:14.000
It's home for the Baxters, but not for Felix.

01:14.000 --> 01:18.000
He remembers the big, yellow moon in Brazil.

01:18.000 --> 01:21.000
Then he remembers his last day in the jungle.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
The two men with white hats.

01:24.000 --> 01:28.000
The big box. The long plane journey.

01:28.000 --> 01:37.000
The shop. Beautiful Birds in New York.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
Felix closes his eyes.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.000
Now he can't see the city and the snow.

01:43.000 --> 01:48.000
He can see other things. He can see the life he loves.

01:48.000 --> 01:53.000
I want to be with my family again, he thinks.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
I want to fly home to the jungle.

01:56.000 --> 02:01.000
It's warm there, and the trees are always green.

02:01.000 --> 02:04.000
He puts his head under one wing.

02:04.000 --> 02:09.000
One day, he says, one day.

02:18.000 --> 02:22.000
One day comes two weeks later.

02:23.000 --> 02:27.000
Mr. Baxter opens Felix's cage to give him some food.

02:27.000 --> 02:31.000
Then he hears the telephone.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.000
Can you answer that, George?

02:34.000 --> 02:36.000
asks Mrs. Baxter.

02:36.000 --> 02:38.000
I'm in the bath.

02:38.000 --> 02:40.000
Okay.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
Says Mr. Baxter.

02:42.000 --> 02:47.000
He goes to the phone, but forgets to shut Felix's cage.

02:47.000 --> 02:50.000
Felix can see an open window.

02:50.000 --> 02:54.000
This is it! he thinks.

02:57.000 --> 03:01.000
He flies out of his cage and out of the window.

03:01.000 --> 03:05.000
The air under his wings is very cold.

03:05.000 --> 03:09.000
Behind him he hears, Hey, Felix!

03:09.000 --> 03:12.000
But he doesn't go back.

03:12.000 --> 03:18.000
He looks down at the streets and buildings and flies through the city.

03:18.000 --> 03:21.000
A girl in a cafe with her mother sees him.

03:21.000 --> 03:22.000
Look!

03:22.000 --> 03:26.000
She says, her mother doesn't hear.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
She's reading her newspaper.

03:39.000 --> 03:42.000
After an hour, Felix stops.

03:42.000 --> 03:46.000
He stands on the head of the Statue of Liberty.

03:47.000 --> 03:49.000
Where are you from?

03:49.000 --> 03:52.000
asks a small, grey and white bird beside him.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
I'm from Brazil.

03:54.000 --> 03:56.000
answers Felix.

03:56.000 --> 03:58.000
And where are you going?

03:58.000 --> 04:00.000
asks the bird.

04:00.000 --> 04:04.000
Felix flies up into the cold, blue sky again.

04:04.000 --> 04:07.000
I'm going home, he says.

04:07.000 --> 04:08.000
Goodbye!

04:17.000 --> 04:19.000
Felix flies south.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
Soon he can't see New York.

04:21.000 --> 04:25.000
All he can see is the Atlantic Ocean.

04:25.000 --> 04:28.000
In the evening the sun starts to go down.

04:28.000 --> 04:32.000
Then the sky is red, yellow and blue.

04:32.000 --> 04:35.000
It's very beautiful.

04:35.000 --> 04:39.000
Felix is hungry, but he's happy too.

04:39.000 --> 04:43.000
For the first time in two years, he's free.

04:43.000 --> 04:46.000
He wants to fly all night.

05:00.000 --> 05:03.000
Two hours later, it starts to rain.

05:03.000 --> 05:06.000
Now the sky's black.

05:06.000 --> 05:10.000
Soon Felix can't see the moon or the stars.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
Where am I?

05:13.000 --> 05:17.000
He remembers his warm cage.

05:17.000 --> 05:20.000
Am I doing the right thing?

05:20.000 --> 05:22.000
He looks down at the cold sea.

05:22.000 --> 05:25.000
Then he sees something.

05:25.000 --> 05:28.000
Is it a star in the black water?

05:28.000 --> 05:31.000
No, it can't be a star.

05:31.000 --> 05:34.000
He looks again.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
It's a ship.

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
Felix flies down to the ship.

05:44.000 --> 05:47.000
There are hundreds of fish on it.

05:47.000 --> 05:50.000
He eats twenty in five minutes.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
Then he sleeps.

05:55.000 --> 05:58.000
In the morning a man on the ship sees him.

05:58.000 --> 05:59.000
Oh no!

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
thinks Felix.

06:00.000 --> 06:02.000
But it's all right.

06:02.000 --> 06:05.000
The man only wants to take a photograph of him.

06:06.000 --> 06:09.000
Felix flies into the sky again.

06:09.000 --> 06:11.000
Good, he thinks.

06:11.000 --> 06:15.000
It's not raining now, and I'm not hungry.

06:22.000 --> 06:26.000
Two days later, Felix flies across Peru.

06:26.000 --> 06:31.000
He looks down and sees the Inca city of Machu Picchu.

06:31.000 --> 06:36.000
Those old stone buildings look interesting, he thinks.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.000
I know.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
I can stop there tonight.

06:41.000 --> 06:44.000
Felix starts to fly down to the buildings.

06:44.000 --> 06:50.000
Then he sees a big bird with beautiful black and white feathers.

06:50.000 --> 06:53.000
It's sitting on a stone.

06:56.000 --> 06:57.000
Hello?

06:57.000 --> 07:00.000
You're not from Peru, are you?

07:00.000 --> 07:02.000
Says the bird.

07:02.000 --> 07:04.000
Felix tells his story.

07:04.000 --> 07:09.000
Two years in a cage in New York! says the bird.

07:09.000 --> 07:12.000
Yes, answers Felix.

07:12.000 --> 07:15.000
But now I'm going home.

07:15.000 --> 07:18.000
Can you tell me how to get there?

07:19.000 --> 07:24.000
I have a friend, Aca in Rio, says the bird.

07:24.000 --> 07:26.000
He knows the jungle.

07:26.000 --> 07:29.000
Go there and ask him.

07:31.000 --> 07:40.000
Felix flies from Peru to Rio.

07:40.000 --> 07:45.000
There he sees a lot of people in the street.

07:45.100 --> 07:49.000
He can hear music and see some birds in a tree.

07:49.100 --> 07:50.000
Is one of them Aca?

07:50.100 --> 07:53.000
Aca! Aca!

07:53.000 --> 07:56.000
He says, yes, that's me.

07:56.300 --> 07:59.000
Answers one of the birds.

07:59.100 --> 08:01.000
Felix can't see him.

08:01.000 --> 08:04.000
Then a boy sees Felix.

08:04.000 --> 08:07.000
Look at the bird. He says to his father.

08:07.000 --> 08:11.000
Can I have him? Can I? Please?

08:15.000 --> 08:20.000
At first, Felix doesn't see the boy or his father.

08:20.000 --> 08:23.000
He's looking at all the birds in the trees.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
Aca! Aca!

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
Says Felix.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
Then there's a warm hand on his neck.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.000
He fights with his wings and his feet.

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
Help! Help!

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
Aca helps him.

08:40.000 --> 08:41.000
Aiiieee!

08:41.000 --> 08:43.000
Says the man.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.000
The two birds fly into the sky.

08:46.000 --> 08:49.000
Thank you. Says Felix.

08:49.000 --> 08:52.000
Then he tells Aca his story.

09:01.000 --> 09:04.000
Felix and Aca fly from Rio to the jungle.

09:04.100 --> 09:10.000
In the evening, Felix says, yes, I remember that village.

09:10.100 --> 09:16.000
My home's very near here. It's only... then he stops.

09:16.100 --> 09:20.000
In front of them there are a lot of men and machines.

09:20.100 --> 09:25.000
Oh no! They're making a new road. Says Aca.

09:25.100 --> 09:30.000
But where's my home? Asks Felix.

09:30.100 --> 09:33.000
And where's my family?

09:33.100 --> 09:37.000
The two birds fly over the new road.

09:37.100 --> 09:40.000
Then they stop in a tree near the village.

09:40.100 --> 09:43.000
Felix is tired and sad.

09:43.100 --> 09:46.000
I'm sorry. Says Aca.

09:46.100 --> 09:52.000
Then Felix sees a small blue and yellow feather in the air.

09:52.100 --> 09:54.000
He looks up.

09:54.100 --> 09:58.000
There above the trees are four birds.

09:58.100 --> 10:02.000
It's them, Aca. He says.

10:02.100 --> 10:04.000
It's my family.

10:04.100 --> 10:08.000
Then he flies into the sky.

10:08.100 --> 10:09.500
The birds see him.

10:09.600 --> 10:11.500
Felix, is it you?

10:11.600 --> 10:16.000
They ask. Yes. Answers Felix.

10:16.100 --> 10:17.500
I'm home!

10:17.500 --> 10:20.000
Squawk! Squawk! Squawk!
